  <p>Prescription drug costs are a top concern for Vernal and Uintah Basin Medicare beneficiaries. The cheapest Part D plan is not always the one with the lowest premium — total cost depends on your specific medications, dosages, and pharmacy.</p>

  <h2>Why the Cheapest Premium Is Not Always the Cheapest Plan</h2>
  <p>A $7/month Part D plan might put your blood pressure medication on Tier 3 with a $47 copay, while a $25/month plan covers the same drug on Tier 1 for $1. Over a year, the "expensive" plan saves you hundreds. We calculate total estimated annual cost — premiums plus copays plus deductible — for each plan based on your actual prescriptions.</p>

  <h2>The $2,000 Out-of-Pocket Cap</h2>
  <p>Starting in 2026, total out-of-pocket spending on Part D drugs is capped at $2,000 per year. Once you reach this limit, the plan covers all remaining prescription costs for the year. Additionally, the Medicare Prescription Payment Plan allows you to spread costs into monthly installments instead of paying large amounts at the pharmacy counter.</p>

  <h2>Pharmacy Choice Affects Cost</h2>
  <p>Part D plans have preferred and standard pharmacy networks. The same drug on the same plan can cost significantly different amounts at different pharmacies. In Vernal, we compare costs at Smith's Pharmacy (1080 W Hwy 40), Walgreens, Walmart (Roosevelt), and mail-order options to find the lowest total cost.</p>

  <h2>Extra Help (Low-Income Subsidy)</h2>
  <p>If your income and resources are limited, you may qualify for Extra Help (also called the Low-Income Subsidy or LIS). Extra Help can reduce your Part D premium, deductible, and copays to near zero. We help Vernal-area residents determine eligibility and apply through Social Security.</p>

  <h2>How to Find Your Cheapest Option</h2>
  <p>Bring your medication list — drug names, dosages, and how often you take each one — and we will compare every available Part D plan in your zip code. The comparison takes about 10–15 minutes and shows estimated annual cost for each plan. There is no charge for this service.</p>

